# Authorized keys for the local `admin` operator account on every fleet device.
# Lives in /etc (persisted by bootc) rather than /var/home/admin/.ssh, which is
# runtime state that image builds don't capture. sshd is pointed here by
# /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/10-school-hardening.conf (AuthorizedKeysFile ... %u).
#
# Two keys, two purposes:
#   1. svk-admin      — the human IT admin, SSHing in from the local network.
#   2. svk-server     — lets the cache/dispenser server SSH *into* this machine
#                       (the jump-host fan-out to LAN-only student/staff devices).

